line_1: 'Tis done, He cry'd: I've gain'd my Point. —
line_2: And thrusting it beyond his Joint,

line_1: Within the small dimensions of a point,
line_2: The shapely limb and lubricated joint,

line_1: And when he spies his member, make his point.
line_2: To hear no motion made that's out of joint,

line_1: Headlong they hurl him on some ice-rock's point,
line_2: Mangle each limb, and dislocate each joint;
